author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Dan Cook)
title: Cape volleyball defeats Caesar Rodney 3-0
text:
Cape volleyball defeats Caesar Rodney 3-0 First win over Riders since 2004 By Dan Cook | Oct 22, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook Cape senior captain Izzie Marsico taps over one of her six kills in the Viking 3-0 win over the Riders. 
Alison Palmer, Izzie Marsico and Abby E'Nama teamed for 20 kills as the Lady Vikings downed the Riders 3-0 Thursday, Oct. 22 at the Cape Henlopen Gymnasium 
The 25-16, 29-27 and 25-18 victory was the first for the Vikings over the Riders in over 11 years. 
Setter Logan Shuttleworth assisted on 25 Cape points in the match. 
"The pressure was on," said Cape assistant coach Pam Coupe. "We dug down deep and they persevered. It's about the team." Cape junior Abby E'Nama taps over one of her five kills in the 3-0 win over Caesar Rodney. (Photo by: Dan Cook) Cape libero Kira Vitella gets low to dig up a Caesar Rodney spike attempt. She had four digs in the contest. (Photo by: Dan Cook)
